abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump said in a tweet he will sign a $738 billion defense bill that sets policy on everything from family leave to fighter jets.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump said in a tweet he will sign a $738 billion defense bill that sets policy on everything from family leave to fighter jets.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump said in a tweet he will sign a $738 billion defense bill that sets policy on everything from family leave to fighter jets.
headline_main: Trump Says He Will Sign Defense Policy Bill After It Clears Congress
headline_print_headline: Trump Says He Will Sign Defense Policy Bill After It Clears Congress

abstract: U.S. Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell on Wednesday said that the Republican-led chamber could start an impeachment trial of President Donald Trump, a fellow Republican, next month.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell on Wednesday said that the Republican-led chamber could start an impeachment trial of President Donald Trump, a fellow Republican, next month.
headline_main: U.S. Senate Could Start Impeachment Trial Next Month: McConnell
headline_print_headline: U.S. Senate Could Start Impeachment Trial Next Month: McConnell

abstract: A year ago, Shoshana Zuboff dropped an intellectual bomb on the technology industry. She hasn’t stood still since.

abstract: Finland's new prime minister said on Wednesday the center-left coalition government had given its "silent blessing" to the Foreign Minister to go ahead with plans to repatriate children of women who traveled to Syria to join Islamic State.
snippet: Finland's new prime minister said on Wednesday the center-left coalition government had given its "silent blessing" to the Foreign Minister to go ahead with plans to repatriate children of women who traveled to Syria to join Islamic State.
lead_paragraph: HELSINKI — Finland's new prime minister said on Wednesday the center-left coalition government had given its "silent blessing" to the Foreign Minister to go ahead with plans to repatriate children of women who traveled to Syria to join Islamic State.
headline_main: New Finland Leader: 'Silent Blessing' Given to Bring Home Islamic State Kids
headline_print_headline: New Finland Leader: 'Silent Blessing' Given to Bring Home Islamic State Kids

abstract: Britain's election on Thursday is widely referred to as the most important in a generation given the impact it will have on the country leaving the European Union and choosing between starkly opposed economic paths.

abstract: Lebanon cannot expect to receive international aid for its battered economy until a new government undertakes serious reforms, diplomats decided at a closed-door meeting in Paris on Wednesday.
snippet: Lebanon cannot expect to receive international aid for its battered economy until a new government undertakes serious reforms, diplomats decided at a closed-door meeting in Paris on Wednesday.
lead_paragraph: PARIS — Lebanon cannot expect to receive international aid for its battered economy until a new government undertakes serious reforms, diplomats decided at a closed-door meeting in Paris on Wednesday.
headline_main: Diplomats to Lebanon: Expect No Aid Before Government Formed
headline_print_headline: Diplomats to Lebanon: Expect No Aid Before Government Formed

abstract: Near the end of a marathon impeachment hearing in the House of Representatives last month, former White House national security aide Fiona Hill tied conservative jabs at George Soros to “the longest-running anti-Semitic trope that we have in history.”
